<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
These specimens represent the shallowest bathymetric records so far for 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Malletiidae" genus="Malletia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Malletia goniura" order="Nuculanida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="goniura">Malletia goniura</taxonomicName>
(836-941 m). It has previously been collected in deeper waters (1,500-3,300 m depth) (
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Coan and Valentich-Scott 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
